As condolences continue to pour in for the late gospel giant Deborah Fraser, Sunday World can confirm that she will be buried at Hillcrest Cemetery in Durban on Saturday. The family announced on Tuesday that her memorial service will be held on Thursday at The House Of Treasures Ministries in Joburg South. The proceedings will start at 1pm. The Abanye Bayombona hitmaker took her last breath at the Chris Hani Baragwanath Academic Hospital in Soweto on Sunday. She was surrounded by her family and close friends when she died. Her funeral is expected to be attended by government officials, her colleagues in the showbiz industry, and members of the community. Gospel singer Deborah Fraser dies after short illness For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.